# shadcn/ui for Guardian

Use **shadcn/ui** components for all UI elements in the Guardian app.

## Components to Use

- **Button**: `import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"` — Primary, secondary, outline, ghost variants
- **Input**: `import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input"` — Form inputs
- **Label**: `import { Label } from "@/components/ui/label"` — Form labels
- **Card**: `import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card"` — Containers
- **Textarea**: `import { Textarea } from "@/components/ui/textarea"` — Multi-line text
- **Tabs**: `import { Tabs, TabsList, TabsTrigger, TabsContent } from "@/components/ui/tabs"` — Tab navigation
- **Badge**: `import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge"` — Status/chips
- **Alert**: `import { Alert, AlertDescription } from "@/components/ui/alert"` — Notifications
- **Table**: `import { Table, TableHeader, TableBody, TableRow, TableCell } from "@/components/ui/table"` — Data tables

## Adding Components

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

## Styling

- Use Tailwind classes via `className`
- Follow shadcn variants: `variant="primary"`, `variant="outline"`, etc.
- Use design tokens from `src/index.css` (CSS variables)

## Do not

- Create custom button/input/card styles when shadcn equivalents exist
- Use inline styles for layout; use Tailwind utilities
